---
import DocsLayout from "../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Pattern: Task Management">
  <h1>Build a Task Manager with EntDB</h1>
  <p>Complete example: task management app with projects, tasks, comments, assignments, and sharing between friends.</p>

  <h2>1. Schema (schema.proto)</h2>
  <pre><code>syntax = "proto3";
import "entdb_options.proto";

enum TaskStatus {"{"}TODO = 0; IN_PROGRESS = 1; DONE = 2;{"}"}
enum Priority   {"{"}LOW = 0; MEDIUM = 1; HIGH = 2; URGENT = 3;{"}"}

message Project {"{"}
    option (entdb.node) = {"{"}
        type_id: 1
        tenant_visible: true
        data_policy: DATA_POLICY_BUSINESS
    {"}"};
    string name = 1        [(entdb.field) = {"{"}required: true, pii_false: true{"}"}];
    string description = 2 [(entdb.field) = {"{"}pii_false: true{"}"}];
{"}"}

message Task {"{"}
    option (entdb.node) = {"{"}
        type_id: 2
        inherit: true
        data_policy: DATA_POLICY_BUSINESS
    {"}"};
    string title = 1       [(entdb.field) = {"{"}required: true, searchable: true, pii_false: true{"}"}];
    TaskStatus status = 2;
    Priority priority = 3;
    string assignee_id = 4 [(entdb.field) = {"{"}pii: true{"}"}];
{"}"}

message Comment {"{"}
    option (entdb.node) = {"{"}
        type_id: 3
        inherit: true
        data_policy: DATA_POLICY_PERSONAL
        subject_field: "author_id"
    {"}"};
    string body = 1        [(entdb.field) = {"{"}required: true, pii: true{"}"}];
    string author_id = 2   [(entdb.field) = {"{"}pii: true{"}"}];
{"}"}

// Edges
message ProjectHasTask {"{"}
    option (entdb.edge) = {"{"}edge_id: 1, name: "HAS_TASK", propagate_share: true{"}"};
    Project from = 15;
    Task to = 16;
{"}"}

message TaskHasComment {"{"}
    option (entdb.edge) = {"{"}edge_id: 2, name: "HAS_COMMENT", propagate_share: true{"}"};
    Task from = 15;
    Comment to = 16;
{"}"}

message TaskAssignedTo {"{"}
    option (entdb.edge) = {"{"}edge_id: 3, name: "ASSIGNED_TO"{"}"};
    Task from = 15;
    User to = 16;
{"}"}</code></pre>

  <h2>2. Generate types</h2>
  <pre><code>entdb generate schema.proto --python myapp/schema.py
entdb init schema.proto</code></pre>

  <h2>3. Connect and create</h2>
  <pre><code>from entdb_sdk import DbClient
from myapp.schema import Project, Task, Comment, ProjectHasTask, TaskHasComment

async with DbClient("localhost:50051") as db:
    # Create project with tasks — atomic
    plan = db.atomic("alice", "user:alice")
    plan.create(Project, {"{"}name": "Q4 Launch"{"}"}, as_="project")
    plan.create(Task, {"{"}title": "Design mockups", "status": "TODO"{"}"}, as_="task1")
    plan.create(Task, {"{"}title": "Backend API", "status": "TODO"{"}"}, as_="task2")
    plan.edge_create(ProjectHasTask, from_="$project.id", to="$task1.id")
    plan.edge_create(ProjectHasTask, from_="$project.id", to="$task2.id")
    result = await plan.commit()

    project_id = result.created_node_ids[0]</code></pre>

  <h2>4. Share with teammates</h2>
  <pre><code># Share the project — tasks are automatically shared (propagate_share)
await db.share(project_id, "user:bob", "write", "alice", granted_by="user:alice")
await db.share(project_id, "user:carol", "read", "alice", granted_by="user:alice")

# Bob can now see AND edit all tasks in the project
# Carol can see but not edit

# Create a group for the team
await db.group_add("team-launch", "user:bob", "alice")
await db.group_add("team-launch", "user:carol", "alice")
await db.group_add("team-launch", "user:dave", "alice")

# Share future projects with the whole group
await db.share(next_project_id, "group:team-launch", "write", "alice", granted_by="user:alice")
# All group members get access. Add new members to the group = instant access.</code></pre>

  <h2>5. Query tasks</h2>
  <pre><code># Alice queries her tasks (automatic ACL filtering)
tasks = await db.query(Task, "alice", "user:alice", filter={"{"}status": "TODO"{"}"})

# Bob queries (sees only what he has access to)
bob_tasks = await db.query(Task, "alice", "user:bob", filter={"{"}status": "TODO"{"}"})

# Get all comments on a task (ACL via parent)
comments = await db.connected(task_id, TaskHasComment, "alice", "user:bob")

# Bob's shared_with_me
shared = await db.shared_with_me("user:bob", "alice")</code></pre>

  <h2>6. Add a comment</h2>
  <pre><code># Bob adds a comment to alice's task (has write access)
plan = db.atomic("alice", "user:bob")
plan.create(Comment, {"{"}body": "Mockups look great!", "author_id": "user:bob"{"}"}, as_="c")
plan.edge_create(TaskHasComment, from_=task_id, to="$c.id")
await plan.commit()</code></pre>

  <h2>7. Read-after-write consistency</h2>
  <pre><code># SDK handles this automatically:
result = await plan.commit()
# Next read is guaranteed to see the write:
task = await db.get(Task, result.created_node_ids[0], "alice", "user:alice")
# task is ALWAYS found. Zero application code needed.</code></pre>

  <h2>What the database handles automatically</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>ACL</strong>: Bob only sees tasks he has access to. No application filtering code.</li>
    <li><strong>Inheritance</strong>: share project = share all tasks + comments under it.</li>
    <li><strong>New items</strong>: task added after sharing → automatically accessible.</li>
    <li><strong>Revoke</strong>: revoke project access → all tasks/comments instantly blocked.</li>
    <li><strong>GDPR</strong>: Bob deletes account → comments anonymized ("Deleted User: Mockups look great!").</li>
    <li><strong>Consistency</strong>: read after write always returns the latest data.</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
